Package: Viperfish
Type: Package
Title: SED Generation for Shark and Stingray Outputs
Version: 0.6.0
Date: 2026-01-13
Author: Aaron Robotham, Claudia Lagos, Rodrigo Tobar
Maintainer: Aaron Robotham <aaron.robotham@uwa.edu.au>
Description: Post-processes ICRAR Shark SAM outputs and Stingray light-cone catalogs
    into galaxy spectral energy distributions (SEDs) and broadband photometry using
    ProSpect. It reads Shark star-formation and metallicity histories, applies
    dust attenuation and re-emission assumptions, and writes consistent tabular
    products for downstream survey and mock-catalog analysis.
License: LGPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.0), ProSpect (>= 0.8.2), data.table, hdf5r
Imports: celestial (>= 1.4.5), bit64, foreach, doSNOW, checkmate, snow, ini, bigmemory
Suggests: knitr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
